body:
Currently, the binding for `SkRect.Location` [here](https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp/blob/5b1d054f88288d9532d91d1639b9c1099d589650/binding/Binding/Definitions.cs#L1668) is given as

```
public SKPoint Location {
            get { return new SKPoint (left, top); }
            set {
                left = value.X;
                top = value.Y; 
            }
        }
```

However, this doesn't just change just the location but also changes the size. So, the ideal one should be offset the bottom and right negatively to make sure the size is the same. 

~~The same also applies to `Offset` by position [here](https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp/blob/5b1d054f88288d9532d91d1639b9c1099d589650/binding/Binding/Definitions.cs#L1798)~~

~~Because the above should be `Offset(pos.X, pos.Y, -pos.X, -pos.Y)` . That would be the correct way to offset a rectangle, semantically.~~

Both of the above are highly misleading currently, and fixing that are breaking changes. So, I'm opening an issue instead of a PR.
